    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-05T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-05T18:00:00-05:00" n="774"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.861/17a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-05T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 5, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3604. 1. It is our plan formally to call the United States mission to Moscow “The
                    President’s Special War Supply Mission to the Union <pb facs="0841" n="829"
                        xml:id="pg_829"/> of Soviet Socialist Republics”.<note n="80"
                        xml:id="d774fn80">This title was later simplified by deletion of the words
                        “War Supply”.</note> Please inform the Department of formal designation of
                    British mission.</p>
                <p>2. Mr. Harriman is being designated as the Special Representative of the
                    President and Chairman of the Special War Supply Mission to the Union of Soviet
                    Socialist Republics with Rank of Ambassador, and the four members listed in my
                    3542, September 2, midnight,<note n="81" xml:id="d774fn81">Not printed.</note>
                    have been designated as Members on the Special War Supply Mission to the Union
                    of Soviet Socialist Republics with the Rank of Minister.</p>
                <p>3. Please inform Department of official ranks of British mission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
